  "title": "Body Foot Therapist Reflexologist",
  "description": "<p>Body Therapists /  Reflexologists must understand how the body's muscles interact and how to treat specific body parts. Body Therapist / Reflexologist works one-on-one with clients, so interpersonal skills and professionalism are  </p>\n<p>essential.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>聘请足疗/按摩治疗师 Job Description:</p>\n<p>1) Massages customers and administers other body conditioning  treatments like alcohol, lubricants, or other rubbing compounds for hygienic or remedial purposes.</p>\n<p>2) Massages body and foot, using such techniques as kneading,  rubbing, and stroking flesh, to stimulate blood circulation, relax  contracted muscles, facilitate the elimination of toxicity, or</p>\n<p>4) May give directions to clients in activities, such as reducing or remedial exercises.</p>\n<p>5) May examine the client and recommend body conditioning activities or treatments.</p>\n<p>6) Able to record treatments furnished to customers.</p>\n<p>Prefer with relevant Diploma / WSQ Certifications &amp; at least 3 years experience</p>\n<p>Looking Body Therapist/ Foot Reflexologist/ Supervisor/ Asst Manager role</p>\n<p>Able to commit on alternate Weekends and PH</p>\n<p>Able to do overtime and might need to do long hours if required</p>\n<p>- 工作经验：有3年或以上工作经验，</p>\n<p>- 上班时间：10:00-22:00，（包括了午餐和晚餐的时间），</p>\n<p>- 良好的个人卫生习卫生习惯</p>\n<p>- 鉴于按摩需要一定的体力 </p>",
